      <scopecontent>
         
         <head>Collection Overview</head>
         
         <p>Correspondence, articles, addresses, and other papers, relating to Farley's career and to the National Educational Association, with which he was associated from 1929-1956, together with personal and genealogical correspondence. Topics include academic freedom, educational television, reading, rural education, illiteracy, opposition to Federal aid to education, charges of communism, the military, and public relations in school.</p><!-- OPTIONAL: Use Arrangement clip here for Collection Arrangement section -->
      
      </scopecontent>
      
